WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:10.260 --> 00:00:13.096 position:50% align:center
Okay, so the major general,

00:00:13.179 --> 00:00:16.725 position:50% align:center
is he against what the
government's been up to?

00:00:16.808 --> 00:00:18.018 position:50% align:center
No.

00:00:21.104 --> 00:00:23.481 position:50% align:center
It seems it's finally arrived.

00:00:26.735 --> 00:00:28.737 position:50% align:center
Karen's mysterious.

00:00:28.820 --> 00:00:33.533 position:50% align:center
Whatever he's after,
no one can be sure.

00:00:33.616 --> 00:00:38.621 position:50% align:center
[alarm buzzes]

00:00:41.875 --> 00:00:46.880 position:50% align:center
[OTHERS growl, groan]

00:00:52.260 --> 00:00:53.470 position:50% align:center
[KAITO]
Hm?

00:00:54.888 --> 00:00:56.431 position:50% align:center
[KAITO'S SUBORDINATE A]
Chief Sumeragi!

00:00:58.516 --> 00:00:59.851 position:50% align:center
There's a swarm of Others!

00:00:59.934 --> 00:01:02.437 position:50% align:center
They've just advanced
into the heart of Suoh!

00:01:02.520 --> 00:01:06.107 position:50% align:center
Others? Then have them
exterminated post-haste!

00:01:06.191 --> 00:01:07.400 position:50% align:center
[KAITO'S SUBORDINATE A]
But I can't, sir.

00:01:07.484 --> 00:01:09.110 position:50% align:center
The defense system
is inoperable!

00:01:09.194 --> 00:01:11.071 position:50% align:center
Psynet isn't working!

00:01:11.154 --> 00:01:13.323 position:50% align:center
[KAITO gasps]
And the council?

00:01:13.406 --> 00:01:14.366 position:50% align:center
[KAITO'S SUBORDINATE A]
I don't know!

00:01:14.449 --> 00:01:16.159 position:50% align:center
There's no way to contact them.

00:01:16.242 --> 00:01:17.702 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:01:17.786 --> 00:01:20.914 position:50% align:center
[KAITO]
So, then. Arahabaki must be...

00:01:27.837 --> 00:01:31.091 position:50% align:center
Karen, why would you do this?

00:01:32.175 --> 00:01:36.805 position:50% align:center
[OTHERS groan]

00:01:44.062 --> 00:01:46.356 position:50% align:center
This time, for certain.

00:01:46.439 --> 00:01:47.941 position:50% align:center
I'll get it back.

00:01:58.326 --> 00:02:03.331 position:50% align:center
[OTHERS AND SOLDIERS shouting]

00:02:08.128 --> 00:02:09.587 position:50% align:center
[HANABI]
Yuito!

00:02:09.671 --> 00:02:13.133 position:50% align:center
Yuito! Hey! Can you hear me?

00:02:15.176 --> 00:02:16.344 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:02:16.428 --> 00:02:18.638 position:50% align:center
[OTHER A growls]

00:02:23.101 --> 00:02:25.270 position:50% align:center
[HANABI] What's the matter?
You need to focus!

00:02:25.353 --> 00:02:26.855 position:50% align:center
Uh, sorry.

00:02:26.938 --> 00:02:28.648 position:50% align:center
[HANABI]
Wataru, are you there?

00:02:28.732 --> 00:02:30.108 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:02:30.191 --> 00:02:31.484 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:02:31.568 --> 00:02:33.278 position:50% align:center
So many. Why?

00:02:33.361 --> 00:02:38.366 position:50% align:center
[OTHERS screaching]

00:02:41.202 --> 00:02:46.207 position:50% align:center
[SOLDIERS, OTHERS grunting]

00:02:47.000 --> 00:02:48.418 position:50% align:center
[shouts]

00:02:53.256 --> 00:02:54.215 position:50% align:center
[YUITO gasps]

00:02:54.299 --> 00:02:55.592 position:50% align:center
Wataru?

00:02:55.675 --> 00:02:57.093 position:50% align:center
[TSUGUMI]
Mm.

00:02:57.177 --> 00:02:59.804 position:50% align:center
No good. He's not responding.

00:03:01.598 --> 00:03:03.725 position:50% align:center
Psynet's down right now.

00:03:03.808 --> 00:03:05.352 position:50% align:center
[WATARU]
Yuito, be careful!

00:03:05.435 --> 00:03:07.187 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
Huh? Wataru?

00:03:07.270 --> 00:03:09.397 position:50% align:center
[WATARU]
Arahabaki shut down,

00:03:09.481 --> 00:03:11.983 position:50% align:center
that's the computer system
that controls Suoh.

00:03:13.151 --> 00:03:15.195 position:50% align:center
[WATARU] The exact cause
is unknown at the moment,

00:03:15.278 --> 00:03:17.614 position:50% align:center
but it's disabled
our defense system.

00:03:17.697 --> 00:03:20.742 position:50% align:center
That's how the Others
managed to invade the city.

00:03:20.825 --> 00:03:22.410 position:50% align:center
Hang on. I-I'm confused.

00:03:22.494 --> 00:03:24.496 position:50% align:center
What's the plan?

00:03:24.579 --> 00:03:27.082 position:50% align:center
[WATARU] I'm speaking
through one-way telepathy.

00:03:27.165 --> 00:03:29.918 position:50% align:center
I'll see if I can get
Psynet back online.

00:03:30.001 --> 00:03:31.670 position:50% align:center
Haruka's out in the field now.

00:03:33.505 --> 00:03:35.423 position:50% align:center
[WATARU]
Mm?

00:03:35.507 --> 00:03:36.716 position:50% align:center
What the--?

00:03:45.850 --> 00:03:48.103 position:50% align:center
[WATARU]
The Seiran Regional Force?

00:03:48.186 --> 00:03:49.229 position:50% align:center
HQ's surrounded!

00:03:49.312 --> 00:03:50.605 position:50% align:center
[SRF SOLDIER A]
What are you doing?

00:03:52.190 --> 00:03:53.525 position:50% align:center
What's wrong?

00:03:53.608 --> 00:03:56.361 position:50% align:center
[WATARU] For now, eliminate as
many Others as possible.

00:03:56.444 --> 00:03:58.029 position:50% align:center
We'll get through this!

00:03:58.113 --> 00:04:01.282 position:50% align:center
If my hunch is right,
it's a coup.

00:04:01.366 --> 00:04:02.659 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:04:02.742 --> 00:04:04.285 position:50% align:center
Hello? You there?

00:04:04.369 --> 00:04:06.371 position:50% align:center
What's up? What'd he say?

00:04:06.454 --> 00:04:08.623 position:50% align:center
He reached me through telepathy.

00:04:08.707 --> 00:04:10.458 position:50% align:center
He said Arahabaki's down.

00:04:10.542 --> 00:04:13.962 position:50% align:center
So's Psynet, which means
there's no defense system.

00:04:14.045 --> 00:04:16.047 position:50% align:center
He believes it's a coup d'etat.

00:04:16.131 --> 00:04:17.507 position:50% align:center
[HANABI]
Really?

00:04:17.590 --> 00:04:20.468 position:50% align:center
[TSUGUMI] Is Major General
Karen responsible for this?

00:04:21.928 --> 00:04:23.138 position:50% align:center
[YUITO grunts]

00:04:26.016 --> 00:04:28.309 position:50% align:center
He's gone too far.

00:04:28.393 --> 00:04:29.853 position:50% align:center
[HANABI]
Mm...

00:04:29.936 --> 00:04:33.231 position:50% align:center
[gasps] Yuito. If he's trying
to overthrow the government,

00:04:33.314 --> 00:04:34.649 position:50% align:center
do you think he'll...?

00:04:34.733 --> 00:04:38.153 position:50% align:center
[gasps]
My dad!

00:04:39.529 --> 00:04:44.534 position:50% align:center
♪

00:06:09.703 --> 00:06:13.081 position:50% align:center
[OTHERS growl]

00:06:13.164 --> 00:06:14.416 position:50% align:center
[GEMMA]
Here's another wave.

00:06:14.499 --> 00:06:15.709 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
I got this!

00:06:17.627 --> 00:06:18.837 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:06:23.883 --> 00:06:25.343 position:50% align:center
[shouts]

00:06:26.594 --> 00:06:29.472 position:50% align:center
[OTHER B shout]

00:06:29.556 --> 00:06:31.307 position:50% align:center
[YUITO exhales]

00:06:31.391 --> 00:06:33.393 position:50% align:center
[HANABI]
Yuito! Your dad--

00:06:33.476 --> 00:06:35.353 position:50% align:center
I mean the chairman,
could be in trouble.

00:06:35.437 --> 00:06:36.438 position:50% align:center
You should go check on him!

00:06:36.521 --> 00:06:37.731 position:50% align:center
[YUITO grunts]

00:06:41.693 --> 00:06:44.070 position:50% align:center
[TSUGUMI] Strange. You'd think
he'd leave right away

00:06:44.154 --> 00:06:46.865 position:50% align:center
to make sure Chief
Sumeragi was alright.

00:06:46.948 --> 00:06:49.242 position:50% align:center
[GEMMA] He won't simply
abandon his duty.

00:06:50.660 --> 00:06:51.870 position:50% align:center
[TSUGUMI gasps]

00:07:00.670 --> 00:07:02.380 position:50% align:center
[KAITO]
What is all this?

00:07:04.424 --> 00:07:07.761 position:50% align:center
[KAITO]
We lost contact? Completely?

00:07:07.844 --> 00:07:11.389 position:50% align:center
Our comms are jammed.
We can't reach the soldiers.

00:07:11.473 --> 00:07:13.141 position:50% align:center
Who's to blame for this?

00:07:14.768 --> 00:07:16.102 position:50% align:center
[LUKA gasps]

00:07:16.186 --> 00:07:18.021 position:50% align:center
[KAITO'S SUBORDINATE C]
Comms connected. Starting video.

00:07:18.104 --> 00:07:19.439 position:50% align:center
[LUKA gasps]

00:07:19.522 --> 00:07:20.565 position:50% align:center
[KAITO'S SUBORDINATE C]
This came from a traffic camera

00:07:20.648 --> 00:07:22.525 position:50% align:center
right before the jamming began.

00:07:26.029 --> 00:07:28.907 position:50% align:center
[KAITO'S SUBORDINATE A] That's
the Seiran Regional Force!

00:07:28.990 --> 00:07:31.659 position:50% align:center
[KAITO, LUKA gasp]

00:07:35.955 --> 00:07:37.916 position:50% align:center
[KAITO grunts]

00:07:37.999 --> 00:07:40.085 position:50% align:center
[KAITO'S SUBORDINATE A] I have
an update, Chief Sumeragi.

00:07:41.711 --> 00:07:42.962 position:50% align:center
[KAITO'S SUBORDINATE A]
Psynet's backup system

00:07:43.046 --> 00:07:45.924 position:50% align:center
and all radio comms are down.
And as you know,

00:07:46.007 --> 00:07:49.594 position:50% align:center
the Seiran Regional Force
has us surrounded.

00:07:49.678 --> 00:07:52.931 position:50% align:center
And as for the underground
evacuation route...

00:07:53.014 --> 00:07:55.809 position:50% align:center
I'm sure the enemy
knows all about it.

00:07:55.892 --> 00:07:59.229 position:50% align:center
And the OSF has
been split into two.

00:07:59.312 --> 00:08:00.563 position:50% align:center
The council?

00:08:00.647 --> 00:08:02.065 position:50% align:center
[KAITO'S SUBORDINATE A]
We still can't get a read

00:08:02.148 --> 00:08:05.485 position:50% align:center
on the situation, and we haven't
located the chairman yet.

00:08:09.072 --> 00:08:10.824 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:08:10.907 --> 00:08:14.119 position:50% align:center
[OTHERS growl]

00:08:26.131 --> 00:08:26.881 position:50% align:center
[HANABI grunts]

00:08:26.965 --> 00:08:28.508 position:50% align:center
[GEMMA grunts]

00:08:28.591 --> 00:08:29.801 position:50% align:center
[TSUGUMI gasps]

00:08:36.975 --> 00:08:39.144 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
What the hell is happening?

00:08:39.227 --> 00:08:41.938 position:50% align:center
Major General Karen
organized a coup?

00:08:42.022 --> 00:08:44.065 position:50% align:center
[ANNOUNCER A] That Other
was slain in a single blow!

00:08:44.149 --> 00:08:47.027 position:50% align:center
And by none other than
Septentrion First Class

00:08:47.110 --> 00:08:50.071 position:50% align:center
"Brain Eater" Major General
Karen Travers!

00:08:50.155 --> 00:08:52.365 position:50% align:center
Whoa! He's so cool!

00:08:52.449 --> 00:08:53.825 position:50% align:center
Uh-huh.

00:08:53.908 --> 00:08:56.745 position:50% align:center
However, the Others represent
a constant threat

00:08:56.828 --> 00:08:59.456 position:50% align:center
to the safety of our nation.

00:08:59.539 --> 00:09:03.001 position:50% align:center
The Scouted Class, with their
innate psionic ability,

00:09:03.084 --> 00:09:04.586 position:50% align:center
and the Volunteer Faction,

00:09:04.669 --> 00:09:07.839 position:50% align:center
with trained psionics,
are equally vital.

00:09:07.922 --> 00:09:10.800 position:50% align:center
If our society is to
overcome this danger...

00:09:12.635 --> 00:09:14.471 position:50% align:center
[KAREN]
Private First Class Sumeragi.

00:09:14.554 --> 00:09:16.765 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
Uh! Sir?

00:09:18.975 --> 00:09:21.478 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
Major General Karen!

00:09:21.561 --> 00:09:25.106 position:50% align:center
Rumor is... the Crows have
already begun to pester you.

00:09:25.190 --> 00:09:26.858 position:50% align:center
Uh, yeah!

00:09:26.941 --> 00:09:29.736 position:50% align:center
Just use the press to
your advantage.

00:09:29.819 --> 00:09:30.945 position:50% align:center
Get your name out.

00:09:31.029 --> 00:09:33.531 position:50% align:center
You'll advance much faster.

00:09:33.615 --> 00:09:36.576 position:50% align:center
You'll be well-trained
under Seto's command.

00:09:36.659 --> 00:09:38.745 position:50% align:center
Give it all that you've got.

00:09:38.828 --> 00:09:40.497 position:50% align:center
I expect great things.

00:09:40.580 --> 00:09:43.625 position:50% align:center
[YUITO gasps]
Thank you, sir!

00:09:43.708 --> 00:09:46.294 position:50% align:center
Well, now! That's great, Yuito!

00:09:46.378 --> 00:09:48.713 position:50% align:center
I heard the Major General
had noticed potential in you

00:09:48.797 --> 00:09:50.507 position:50% align:center
ever since you
were in training.

00:09:50.590 --> 00:09:52.509 position:50% align:center
What? Is that true?

00:09:52.592 --> 00:09:54.469 position:50% align:center
Yes. And that means
that you've got

00:09:54.552 --> 00:09:57.138 position:50% align:center
a Septentrion First Class
rooting for you.

00:09:57.222 --> 00:09:58.390 position:50% align:center
Make us proud.

00:09:58.473 --> 00:10:00.517 position:50% align:center
[YUITO gasps]
Right!

00:10:04.229 --> 00:10:06.815 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
The way Nagi suddenly changed.

00:10:06.898 --> 00:10:10.276 position:50% align:center
Could the government be
involved with that, too?

00:10:10.360 --> 00:10:14.114 position:50% align:center
Why would Major General
Karen take things so far?

00:10:14.197 --> 00:10:16.366 position:50% align:center
Maybe Dad knows something
about all this.

00:10:24.708 --> 00:10:26.793 position:50% align:center
Whoa. That was rough!

00:10:29.337 --> 00:10:31.923 position:50% align:center
--[TSUGUMI gasps]
--[GEMMA] Hm? What's wrong?

00:10:32.007 --> 00:10:33.633 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:10:33.717 --> 00:10:35.927 position:50% align:center
Major General Fubuki
is coming this way.

00:10:36.011 --> 00:10:36.761 position:50% align:center
[YUITO. GEMMA, HANABI gasp]

00:10:36.845 --> 00:10:38.179 position:50% align:center
He's straight ahead.

00:10:45.145 --> 00:10:47.939 position:50% align:center
You four, which platoon are you?

00:10:48.023 --> 00:10:50.442 position:50% align:center
Seto Platoon, but he was...

00:10:50.525 --> 00:10:51.776 position:50% align:center
[TSUGUMI]
Killed in action.

00:10:51.860 --> 00:10:53.528 position:50% align:center
So, we're sort of...

00:10:53.611 --> 00:10:56.489 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI]
What? Seto was lost?

00:10:56.573 --> 00:10:59.451 position:50% align:center
Wait. Are you working for
Major General Karen?

00:10:59.534 --> 00:11:01.161 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
Uh, no, sir!

00:11:01.244 --> 00:11:04.581 position:50% align:center
Pardon me, sir.
Please allow me to explain.

00:11:04.664 --> 00:11:05.874 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:11:08.626 --> 00:11:10.211 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI]
I understand.

00:11:10.295 --> 00:11:14.799 position:50% align:center
So then, Gemma was the only OSF
member who received that order.

00:11:14.883 --> 00:11:16.343 position:50% align:center
Yes, sir.

00:11:16.426 --> 00:11:18.178 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI] And I see now that
he's working with what's left

00:11:18.261 --> 00:11:19.679 position:50% align:center
of Seto platoon,

00:11:19.763 --> 00:11:23.475 position:50% align:center
which means he's no longer
cooperating with Karen.

00:11:23.558 --> 00:11:25.477 position:50% align:center
Am I correct to assume that?

00:11:25.560 --> 00:11:27.187 position:50% align:center
Yes, that's right.

00:11:27.270 --> 00:11:30.982 position:50% align:center
Excellent. I need everybody
that I can get.

00:11:31.066 --> 00:11:34.069 position:50% align:center
Starting right now,
you're all part of my unit.

00:11:34.152 --> 00:11:35.612 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
Sir!

00:11:35.695 --> 00:11:38.823 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI] Even I don't have a
complete grasp of the situation.

00:11:38.907 --> 00:11:41.034 position:50% align:center
All that's certain is the
Seiran Regional Force

00:11:41.117 --> 00:11:42.994 position:50% align:center
and other entities
have conspired to launch

00:11:43.078 --> 00:11:46.706 position:50% align:center
a large-scale attack upon Suoh.

00:11:46.790 --> 00:11:49.292 position:50% align:center
And Karen is behind it.

00:11:49.376 --> 00:11:50.460 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:11:50.543 --> 00:11:53.254 position:50% align:center
[HANABI] Innocent people
are getting hurt.

00:11:53.338 --> 00:11:56.424 position:50% align:center
Yes. We're evacuating civilians
who couldn't get out of the city

00:11:56.508 --> 00:12:00.887 position:50% align:center
in time, but I need you four
for something else first.

00:12:01.971 --> 00:12:04.349 position:50% align:center
Go check on the chairman
and all the council members.

00:12:04.432 --> 00:12:06.101 position:50% align:center
Make sure they're safe.

00:12:06.184 --> 00:12:07.686 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:12:07.769 --> 00:12:10.397 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI] They evacuated late,
but they should be on the move.

00:12:10.480 --> 00:12:12.982 position:50% align:center
They're heading to a
shelter as we speak.

00:12:13.066 --> 00:12:14.067 position:50% align:center
[HANABI gasps]

00:12:14.150 --> 00:12:17.153 position:50% align:center
OSF went, and NDF as well,

00:12:17.237 --> 00:12:19.739 position:50% align:center
but we've lost
contact with them.

00:12:19.823 --> 00:12:22.200 position:50% align:center
I'm sure the chairman will be
relieved to see you, though.

00:12:22.283 --> 00:12:25.036 position:50% align:center
[gasps]
Got it.

00:12:25.120 --> 00:12:27.247 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI]
Remember, be cautious.

00:12:27.330 --> 00:12:29.916 position:50% align:center
Not all OSF members
will be on your side.

00:12:32.085 --> 00:12:33.795 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:12:38.299 --> 00:12:39.551 position:50% align:center
[KAITO'S SUBORDINATE A]
The Seiran Regional Force

00:12:39.634 --> 00:12:41.344 position:50% align:center
has yet to make a move.

00:12:41.428 --> 00:12:43.263 position:50% align:center
Are they trying to buy time?

00:12:43.346 --> 00:12:45.098 position:50% align:center
I don't know.

00:12:45.181 --> 00:12:48.810 position:50% align:center
[KAITO] Is it a tactic to
keep us from moving?

00:12:48.893 --> 00:12:51.604 position:50% align:center
What are you plotting, Karen?

00:12:58.153 --> 00:12:59.362 position:50% align:center
[LUKA]
Brother...

00:13:06.870 --> 00:13:09.539 position:50% align:center
This whole thing
is just so awful.

00:13:09.622 --> 00:13:10.582 position:50% align:center
I know.

00:13:10.665 --> 00:13:13.251 position:50% align:center
The city's been
turned upside-down.

00:13:13.335 --> 00:13:15.920 position:50% align:center
[HANABI] It's hard to believe
people with no psionic power

00:13:16.004 --> 00:13:19.215 position:50% align:center
see the world like this
all the time, huh?

00:13:19.299 --> 00:13:20.800 position:50% align:center
[LUKA] That's because
duds aren't connected

00:13:20.884 --> 00:13:22.552 position:50% align:center
to Psynet like we are.

